file list shows only outputs, which is interesting. It seems the supervisor may have hallucinated on those created files. I think it’s crucial to check if the exact files are absent. Also, I might want to inspect the dispatch and activation plan since it seems the session ID was reused, suggesting the agent persisted across activations. This might be key to understanding the task, but it raises questions about fresh activation guarantees.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Validating session status**\\n\\nI'm considering inspecting the operator session, but that might not be applicable here. It's worth mentioning that no checkpoint or status was created, despite some claims. I should also validate whether the compiled file exists and possibly check its structure. Maybe focusing on these details will be enough to clarify what's happening. It feels important to ensure everything aligns with the expectations set by the claims.\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"Accomplished a fresh probe with the canonical primitive:\n\n- I created a new isolated bootstrap at `content_factory_block2/runtime_realcheck/run_009/`\n- I invoked the supervisor via:\n  - `exec` → `openclaw agent --agent sm_s3_visual_planning --message ... --json`\n- That produced a new S3 run under:\n  - `runtime_realcheck/run_009/b2/sectors/s3_visual_planning/`\n\nWhat this proved:\n- `sm_s3_visual_planning` is invokable through the real `openclaw agent` CLI path.\n- In that real turn, it successfully:\n  - read the persisted bootstrap from disk\n  - generated `operator_activation_plan.json`\n  - generated `dispatch/human_subject_extractor_job.json`\n  - wrote `checkpoints/s3_supervisor_started.json`\n  - wrote `compiled/compiled_entities.json`\n  - wrote `compiled/s3_sector_report.md`\n  - wrote `checkpoints/s3_final_checkpoint.json`\n- The final checkpoint is honest:\n  - `status = degraded_completed`\n  - reason = ACP backend unavailable + only one operator path executed\n\nImportant production-faithful findings:\n1. **The decisive hop `supervisor -> real operator` is still not proven.**\n   - The final checkpoint explicitly says the real operator could not be launched:\n     - `ACP runtime backend unavailable; the real op_s3_human_subject_extractor agent could not be launched.`\n   - So Perseus still cannot rely on a real nested operator launch from the supervisor.\n\n2. **Fresh activation is only partially faithful today.**\n   - The `openclaw agent` invocation succeeded as a fresh external CLI activation.\n   - But the run metadata shows it reused the existing supervisor session id:\n     - `sessionId = bc044f1b-d2c1-4419-a020-11428bd36621`\n   - So this is **not** a guaranteed “new session per activation” model yet; it is more like a new turn routed into the same agent session.\n\n3. **The supervisor over-reported some artifacts in chat.**\n   - Its returned summary claimed it created operator `checkpoint.json` and `status.json`.\n   - In the actual `run_009` filesystem, the files present are:\n     - `checkpoints/operator_activation_plan.json`\n     - `checkpoints/s3_bootstrap_ready.json`\n     - `checkpoints/s3_final_checkpoint.json`\n     - `checkpoints/s3_supervisor_started.json`\n     - `compiled/compiled_entities.json`\n     - `compiled/s3_sector_report.md`\n     - `dispatch/human_subject_extractor_job.json`\n     - `inputs/s3_source_package.json`\n     - `operators/human_subject_extractor/output.json`\n   - So the supervisor’s conversational summary is not fully trustworthy; disk remains the source of truth.\n\nHow close this is to production:\n- **Closer than before**, because this was a real top-level supervisor activation through the canonical CLI, against persisted runtime files only.\n- **Still not production-ready**, because the critical nested execution path is broken and activation is not truly session-fresh in the strict sense.\n\nWhat still blocks Perseus:\n- **Main blocker:** ACP/acpx runtime backend is not configured for nested supervisor-launched operator execution.\n- **Secondary blocker:** `openclaw agent` currently appears to reuse the same supervisor session rather than forcing a new session per activation, which is weaker than the intended production assumption.\n- **Operational blocker:** the supervisor can claim artifacts that do not actually exist, so downstream trust must stay file-based until this is corrected.\n\nNet:\n- Proven: **real `exec + openclaw agent` supervisor turn** for `sm_s3_visual_planning`.\n- Not proven: **real supervisor-controlled operator launch**.\n- Verdict: **Perseus should still wait.**","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09720d3158cc1b3e0169cffc0156748191b0c9063361e1410a\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1166,"output":1037,"cacheRead":116352,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":118555,"cost":{"input":0.002915,"output":0.015555000000000001,"cacheRead":0.029088,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.047558}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775238131935,"responseId":"resp_09720d3158cc1b3e0169cffbf450e08191a4136799204974a3"}}
